data.label: About Dinogram
data.content:
What is Dinogram?

Dinogram is an all-in-one application for diagramming, note-taking, brainstorming, and more.


Why I Built Dinogram

During the early stages of project planning, I often find myself juggling multiple applications, each serving a different purpose:


  • Long-form notes in Obsidian, Notion, or Google Docs
  • Diagrams in Miro, Diagrams.net, or Google Draw
  • Sketches and simple drawings in Photoshop, Illustrator, or Affinity Photo
  • Embedded videos, which some applications support but often with limitations


What Does Dinogram Do?

Dinogram brings all of these different content types into one place.


  • Need to take notes? Use the built-in Rich Text Editor for long-form writing.
  • Creating a diagram? Choose from a variety of icons and shapes, or add your own images via an image URL.
  • Want to sketch or draw? Use Dinogram’s basic drawing tool for quick visualizations.
  • Embedding content? No problem! Dinogram supports:
  • Video – Embed videos via a direct MP4 URL or a YouTube link.
  • Code – Powered by the Monaco Editor (the same tech behind VS Code), Dinogram supports syntax highlighting for many commonly used languages.
  • Web Pages – Embed websites via an iframe (note that some sites may block embedding).
  • With Dinogram, you no longer need to switch between multiple apps—everything is in one place.

Configure using the layer properties panel
You can adjust the stacking order (drag and drop), delete, toggle visibility and lock elements and lines using the layers panel.
Note that selected layers always appear on top, but will respect the stacking order when unselected.
Roadmap

Development Roadmap

Dinogram is still in early development, I'm currently rolling out bug fixes and features on the daily.


Please Be Patient

Please be patient if you encounter bugs, performance issues or any other unexpected behaviors.

This project is a pretty massive undertaking with a lot of moving pieces.
